cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a framework for anomaly detection using a geometric anomaly measure and a random forest-based algorithm. This involves machine learning techniques and data analysis, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
